# Backend (Go) rules

- **Architecture (mandatory):** the `masterfabric-go` repo structure must be used once delivered. Do not
  build a custom architecture. Current `main.go` is a temporary `/health` stub — replace it, don't extend it.
- Standard library only unless a package already exists in `go.mod`
- Always expose `GET /health` returning `{"status":"ok"}`
- Default port `8080`; override with `PORT` env var
- CORS is handled in `main.go` `corsMiddleware` — extend the allowed origins list, do not replace it
- Run: `cd backend && go run main.go`
- No raw imagery in request/response bodies — anonymize before persistence (see `docs/PRIVACY.md`)
- Low-confidence AI outputs: mark as `needs_review`, do not present as facts
- No external HTTP calls without timeout context
